    "body": "### Details\r\n\r\nThis PR updates the `Sing Up` flow.\r\n\r\n### Flows\r\n\r\n#### Sign Up\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9729923/110635503-d5bd1580-81b3-11eb-99f8-2fd71a8f74ba.mp4\r\n\r\n#### Magic Link\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9729923/110635721-1583fd00-81b4-11eb-8a49-c5bb925ede19.mp4\r\n\r\n### Test\r\n\r\n#### Sign Up\r\n1. Start `Simplenote` from scratch.\r\n2. Tap on `SIGN UP`.\r\n3. Enter your `Email` and click the `SIGN UP` button.\r\n3. Verify that the `Confirmation` screen is shown.\r\n4. Verify that the email your entered is shown in bold.\r\n5. Verify that the `support@simplenote.com` link redirects to opening your email client, ready to send an email to Simplenote support.\r\n\r\n#### Magic Link\r\n1. Wait for the email, with the magic link, to arrive.\r\n2. Click on the magic link.\r\n3. Verify that you are redirected to the browser to complete the `Sign Up` process.\r\n4. Verify that your `Email` is pre-filled.\r\n5. Enter your `Password` and click the `Sign up` button.\r\n6. Verify that you are redirected to the `Simplenote` app and the `Sign Up` process is complete.\r\n7. Verify that the `Welcome to Simplenote` note is present.\r\n8. Go to `Setting` and verify that your account is the expected one.\r\n\r\n### Review\r\n\r\nOnly one developer and one designer are required to review these changes, anyone can perform the review, but it is recommended that as many developers are possible are involved so that the overall solution ends up being the intended one, without unforeseeable side effects.\r\n\r\n### Release\r\n\r\nThese changes might need release notes.\r\n",
